trans-unit.source: Exception occurs if input dataset is not valid.
trans-unit.target: Exception occurs if input dataset is not valid.

trans-unit.source: This error can appear in many contexts and there is not a single resolution.
trans-unit.target: This error can appear in many contexts and there is not a single resolution.

trans-unit.source: Some modules require a label column, while others require that data be categorical.
trans-unit.target: Some modules require a label column, while others require that data be categorical.

trans-unit.source: Others might require a specific data type.
trans-unit.target: Others might require a specific data type.

trans-unit.source: Review the help topic for the module for which the dataset is used as input, to ascertain if there are any requirements.
trans-unit.target: Review the help topic for the module for which the dataset is used as input, to ascertain if there are any requirements.

trans-unit.source: In some cases, the data itself can be in the wrong format.
trans-unit.target: In some cases, the data itself can be in the wrong format.

trans-unit.source: Data that has been imported from a CSV file can contains bad values, and many datasets can contain missing values.
trans-unit.target: Data that has been imported from a CSV file can contains bad values, and many datasets can contain missing values.
